1. Software path

    Move the software to

        /srv/bloonix/webgui

    After that the directory content looks like:

        #> ls /srv/bloonix/webgui/
        bin  build-all  build-jslib  build-lang  build-package  build-timezone  ChangeLog
        etc  INSTALL  lang  lib  LICENSE  public  schema  source  templates

    Change the owner of the files:

        chown bloonix:bloonix /srv/bloonix
        chown -R bloonix:bloonix /srv/bloonix/webgui

        # Replace www-data with the group of the Nginx webserver
        chgrp -R www-data /srv/bloonix/webgui/public

2. Configuration

    Create the configuration directory for the webgui.

        mkdir /etc/bloonix/webgui

    Copy the configuration to the software directory

        cp /srv/bloonix/webgui/etc/bloonix/webgui/main.conf /etc/bloonix/webgui/

    Make your changes in the configuration file (database password...)

    Create the Nginx configuration. An example can be found in

        /srv/bloonix/webgui/etc/bloonix/webgui/nginx.conf

3. Database

    Create the Elasticsearch template and PostgreSQL database schema.

    Enter the directory "schema" and follow the instruction from the README file.

4. Login

    The login to the webgui is

        admin/admin

5. Have fun :-)

